command_storage.book_storage.SavedItem.t: This book allows you to apply basic settings to an armor stand. Clicking the coloured links will adjust the closest armor stand within three blocks.

Turn gravity off before nudging the Y-position.

Relative Aligned nudging moves the armor stand relative to the player's position and aligned to the block grid.  (X=Left/Right, Z=Away/Towards)

Relative Aligned nudging moves the armor stand relative to the player's exact position.  (X=Left/Right, Y=Above/Below, Z=Away/Towards)

Nudges are in 16ths of a block to align with the pixels of the block textures.

The angle step (default 15°) is used for both the stand rotation and the pose adjustments.

Toward and Away turn the armor stand to face toward or away from you.
Points selected appendage at head or feet.

The Death pose is for a figure lying down and requires a separate armor stand for the legs.

Randomized creates a completely unique randomized custom pose.

The Block and Item presets are designed to hold blocks and items in line with the world grid.
The angle step set for adjusting the stand rotation is also used for the pose adjustments.
Pose and position an armor stand to align a held block or item with an adjacent block.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a block held by it appears on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that an item held by it appears upright on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a non-tool item held by it appears flat on the surface.
Align an armor stand placed on a surface so that a tool held by it appears flat on the surface.

Align an armor stand with a tripwire hook on the wall above it so that a tool held by it appears to be hanging up.

Also locks the armor stand and disables all slots except the mainhand.
Mirroring copies the arm or leg pose from left to right or vice versa. Flipping reverses the armor stand's pose entirely.

Copying an armor stand stores it's settings and pose in the book and these can then be pasted into another armor stand. The book must be the selected item in your mainhand or offhand for this to work.

Locking an armor stand prevents it from being changed using the book and disables interaction with the equipment slots.

Sealing an armor stand, which is only available in creative mode, does the same and in addition makes it invulnerable

To make an item frame invisible it must be one block in front of the players eyes and have an item in the frame.
Alternatively you can also enter:
/trigger if_invisible
To make the item frame visible remove its item.

Must be in creative to make item frame Fixed, or have it enabled from the admin menu.
